Mexican Stocks: Cemex, Empresas ICA, Grupo Mexico, Mexichem

-- B y   L e o n   L a z a r o f f
-- 
2011-09-22T15:51:04Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-22/mexican-stocks-cemex-empresas-ica-grupo-mexico-mexichem.html
The following companies are having
unusual price changes in  Mexico  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 11:36 a.m.  New York  time.  The IPC index fell 3.6 percent to 32,808.74.  Mexican stocks fell the most in six weeks after the  Federal
Reserve ’s warning of “significant downside risks” in the  U.S.
economy . The U.S. is Mexico’s largest trading partner.  Cemex SAB (CEMEXCPO MM), the largest cement maker in the
Americas, plunged 7.4 percent to 5 pesos.  Empresas ICA SAB (ICA* MM), Mexico’s biggest construction
company, lost 5.4 percent, the most in six weeks, to 16.31
pesos.  Mexichem SAB (MEXCHEM* MM), the largest maker of plastic
pipes in  Latin America , declined 5.6 percent, the most in six
weeks, to 42.65 pesos.  Grupo Mexico  SAB (GMEXICOB MM), Mexico’s largest mining
company, dropped 5.8 percent to 32.18 pesos, its lowest price in
almost 14 months as copper declined to a one-year low on the
Comex in New York, falling 8 percent to $3.462 a pound. Grupo
Mexico owns  Southern Copper Corp. (SCCO) , which accounts for about two-
thirds of its revenue.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Leon Lazaroff in New York at 
